{"cursor":"4757","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n which can be customized]]\n\n are customizable by third-party software.]]\n\nA 'context menu' (also called 'contextual', 'shortcut', and 'popup' or 'pop-up'\n'menu') is a menu in a graphical user interface (GUI) that appears upon user\ninteraction, such as a right-click mouse operation. A context menu offers a\nlimited set of choices that are available in the current state, or context, of\nthe operating system or application. Usually the available choices are actions\nrelated to the selected object.\n","linknr":217,"url":"Context_menu","recorded":1362553742,"links":31,"instances":["computing","computing","user_interface","window_manager"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Graphical user interface elements","GUI widgets","Windows administration","Mac OS user interface"],"headings":["History","Implementation","Usability","In documentation","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b5/Context_menu.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/50/Context_menu_windows.png/233px-Context_menu_windows.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["menu","computing"],["mouse","computing#operation"],["selection","user_interface"],["focus","computing"],["sawfish","window_manager"]],"members":["mouse","menu","focus","selection","sawfish"],"related":["Menu_(computing)","Graphical_user_interface","Select